It's a great app, I would definitely give it 5 stars, if it weren't for the constant errors and such; it crashes and freezes way too much. And I don't even want to update it, because people seem to have had issues with the update. I've also added missing characters from video games and manga/anime, some of which seem to have disappeared from the list, because I can't find them after trying to add them. Not all of them have disappeared, but it looks like some have.   Another thing is that some characters are listed twice, and there are those that don't have any description, which I think should be the name of the source that they're from. Some of them even have a lacking description, in other words no mention of their source but something else that describes them. I've also tried submitting pictures of characters that don't have one, but they still haven't been validated. I've only submitted official artwork so it could be seen what the character looks like. I've seen fanarts on a few characters, and I don't think they should be posted. Overall it's a great game, very fun, but if the aspects I mentioned were fixed, it would deserve 5 stars and more.  //It's not so good after the recent update. It's okay but the version before the latest 'update' was a lot better, if you ask me. It doesn't seem to show the rank and experience points anymore which was a nice part of the game. And it's not the game's fault, but after I copied the data from my old phone to a new one, I lost all of the prizes and coins; I had a lot of them. I still have them in the old one, but I'd like to have them in the new one too and play on that, since the old phone hardly works anymore. I can't access the app on my old phone anymore because it fails to connect to Google Play. I really liked Akinator but the recent 'updates' made it worse. And I wish I could restore all the prizes and coins to my new phone.

The game is fun, and the character database is huge. A few too many redundant questions, e.g. being asked four times if my character was female and in three different ways, so that one exact same question was actually asked of me twice.
